					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3090359#post-4280178</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3090359/scp-2694#post-4280178</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 14 Jun 2019 05:30:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Soultear</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1808168</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The idea is ok, but I personally can't stand &quot;crazy-talk&quot; diaries anymore when the article doesn't back it up with a cool explanation. It has become a kind of crutch some skips use. Sort of like a &quot;get out of a dialogue/interrogation/origin story free&quot; card. Lazy and unoriginal. I would just remove that whole segment and come up with something else.</p> <p>Downvoted.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
